==Righteousness in Hinduism==
This is an important term in Hinduism, too (and in Buddhism).
http://www.radiosai.org/pages/thought.asp, for example here:

"19th November 2009 Ladies Day
Thought for the day
What we have to safeguard and protect today are Truth and Righteousness and not the nation. When Truth and Righteousness are protected, they will protect the nation. Hence, righteousness should be fostered in every home............"

One can build a little section for the article's page.

